text: The 5th District of the Wisconsin Senate is located in Southern Wisconsin, and is composed of parts of Milwaukee County, and Waukesha County.District Map ==Current elected officials== Dale P. Kooyenga is the senator serving the 5th district. He was first elected in 2018. Before serving as a senator, he held an office in the State Assembly, serving the 14th District from 2011 to 2019. The area of the 5th Senate District contains three State Assembly Districts:District Map * The 13th (represented by Rob Hutton) * The 14th (represented by Robyn Vining) * The 15th (represented by Joe Sanfelippo) The district is also located mostly within Wisconsin's 5th congressional district, which is represented by U.S. Representative Jim Sensenbrenner.Congressional District Map ==Past senators== A list of all previous senators from this district:Wisconsin Blue Book, 1991-92 edition, Statistics: History, pages 657-666. {| class=wikitable style="text-align:center" !
